  Fishery production developed further. Output of aquatic 
products reached 1.9036 million tonnes, an increase of 19 
percent over 1992. Of this, output of freshwater products 
amounted to 190,000 tonnes, up 41 percent and for saltwater, 
1.7136 million tons, up 17 percent. Famous brand, special, and 
quality aquatic products developed remarkably on a large scale. 
  Conditions for rural production further improved. By the 
end of 1993, the aggregate power capacity of farm machinery 
reached 6.935 million kilowatts, an increase of 7.4 percent over 
the previous year. There were 153,100 small tractors, up 3.3 
percent, and 16,500 trucks for farming purposes, up 10.7 
percent. A total of 922,400 tonnes (in terms of 100 percent 
ingredients) of chemical fertilizers were applied in 1993, a 
drop of 0.9 percent from 1992. Rural areas consumed 2.917 
billion kwh of electricity, up 8.4 percent. Irrigated areas 
increased by 138,600 mu. 
<H5>  2. Industry and Construction </H5>
  Fujian's industrial economy developed rapidly in 1993. The 
output value of industry totaled 36.226 billion yuan, an 
increase of 44 percent over the previous year, the highest 
growth registered since reform and opening up. Light industry 
developed comprehensively, with an added value of 21.781 billion 
yuan, an increase of 50 percent over 1992. Added value of heavy 
industry amounted to 14.445 billion yuan, up 34 percent. 
  Of various economic sectors, industry in the nonpublic 
sector 
maintained its momentum, and state sector industry developed 
rapidly. Added value in the state industry totaled 12.151 
billion yuan, an increase of 9.3 percent over 1992; the 
collective sector, 14.828 billion yuan, up 65 percent; and the 
three kinds of foreign-funded enterprises, 6.011 billion yuan, 
up 68 percent. 
  In the face of fierce market competition, industrial 
enterprises accelerated the readjustment of their product mix. 


